(1631,	'Of Mice and Men',	0,	'John Steinbeck, J. Steinbeck, John Steinbeck, john steinbek, John Steinback',	'unknown',	'1963-01-01 00:00:00',	'The second book in John Steinbeck’s labor trilogy, Of Mice and Men is a touching tale of two migrant laborers in search of work and eventual liberation from their social circumstances. Fiercely devoted to one another, George and Lennie plan to save up to finance their dream of someday owning a small piece of land. The pair seems unstoppable until tragedy strikes and their hopes come crashing down, forcing George to make a difficult decision regarding the welfare of his best friend.

